                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.31,
                                "byte_start": 92742,
                                "byte_stop": 142061,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 99-1864, Hunt against Cromartie and a companion case will be announced by Justice Breyer."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12.31,
                        "stop": 425.221,
                        "byte_start": 142061,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15139,
                            "name": "Stephen G. Breyer",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/stephen_g_breyer",
                            "last_name": "Breyer",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2785,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 775890000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2785"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32682,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49908,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/stephen_g_breyer_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 7777,
                            "identifier": "stephen_g_breyer"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 12.31,
                                "stop": 25.25,
                                "byte_start": 142061,
                                "byte_stop": 193784,
                                "text": "This is the fourth time that this Court has considered an equal protection challenge to North Carolina\u0027s heavily minority, Twelfth Congressional District."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.25,
                                "stop": 40.233,
                                "byte_start": 193784,
                                "byte_stop": 253761,
                                "text": "The legislature initially drew that District\u2019s boundaries in 1992, creating a long narrow ugly shaped district with a majority of African-American voters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.233,
                                "stop": 55.613,
                                "byte_start": 253761,
                                "byte_stop": 315201,
                                "text": "A group of voters brought a case in Federal Court challenging the District\u2019s constitutionality on the ground that the legislature had drawn its boundaries primarily on the basis of race."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.613,
                                "stop": 63.491,
                                "byte_start": 315201,
                                "byte_stop": 346757,
                                "text": "In 1993, this Court held that the voters could proceed with their constitutional challenge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.491,
                                "stop": 89.591,
                                "byte_start": 346757,
                                "byte_stop": 451142,
                                "text": "In 1996, the court held for the voters on the merits, the evidence showed that the District\u2019s boundaries violated the Equal Protection Clause because when the legislature drew those boundaries, considerations of race, for example, a desire to create an African-American majority, were predominant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.591,
                                "stop": 106.046,
                                "byte_start": 451142,
                                "byte_stop": 516971,
                                "text": "In 1999, we considered a new, but similar challenge to a new District 12\u2019s boundaries which the legislature had modified in 1997 in light of our earlier opinions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.046,
                                "stop": 117.212,
                                "byte_start": 516971,
                                "byte_stop": 561692,
                                "text": "The District Court had decided through summary judgment procedures before trial that the boundaries still violated the Equal Protection Clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.212,
                                "stop": 120.87,
                                "byte_start": 561692,
                                "byte_stop": 576321,
                                "text": "The legislature had not changed them enough."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.87,
                                "stop": 126.328,
                                "byte_start": 576321,
                                "byte_stop": 598055,
                                "text": "We objected to the manner in which the District Court reached this conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.328,
                                "stop": 129.182,
                                "byte_start": 598055,
                                "byte_stop": 609549,
                                "text": "There were important factual disagreements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.182,
                                "stop": 135.413,
                                "byte_start": 609549,
                                "byte_stop": 634417,
                                "text": "Summary judgment was not appropriate and we remanded for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.413,
                                "stop": 140.44,
                                "byte_start": 634417,
                                "byte_stop": 654584,
                                "text": "We now, consider the results of those further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.44,
                                "stop": 143.269,
                                "byte_start": 654584,
                                "byte_stop": 665869,
                                "text": "The District Court held a full trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.269,
                                "stop": 152.278,
                                "byte_start": 665869,
                                "byte_stop": 701918,
                                "text": "It considered all the evidence and yet again decided in favor of those who were challenging the district."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 152.278,
                                "stop": 167.075,
                                "byte_start": 701918,
                                "byte_stop": 761059,
                                "text": "It concluded that the legislature when redrawing the boundaries of what is not quite a majority-minority district had continued improperly to take race into account."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.075,
                                "stop": 176.844,
                                "byte_start": 761059,
                                "byte_stop": 800138,
                                "text": "Now, after reviewing the Trial Court record we today find the Trial Court\u2019s decision clearly erroneous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.844,
                                "stop": 185.91,
                                "byte_start": 800138,
                                "byte_stop": 836396,
                                "text": "The legislature\u2019s redrawn District 12 boundaries, in our view, do not violate the Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.91,
                                "stop": 198.118,
                                "byte_start": 836396,
                                "byte_stop": 885297,
                                "text": "In reaching this conclusion we apply standards drawn from this Court\u2019s earlier cases on race based majority-minority legislative districting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.118,
                                "stop": 214.37,
                                "byte_start": 885297,
                                "byte_stop": 950290,
                                "text": "To win, those who challenge such a district, must show that the \u201clegislature subordinated traditional race neutral districting principles to racial considerations\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.37,
                                "stop": 243.523,
                                "byte_start": 950290,
                                "byte_stop": 1066900,
                                "text": "Race must not simply have been \u201ca motivation for the drawing of a majority-minority district, but the predominating factor, motivating the legislature\u2019s districting decisions\u201d, and those who challenge have to show that a facially neutral law was \u201cunexplainable on grounds other than race\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.523,
                                "stop": 267.836,
                                "byte_start": 1066900,
                                "byte_stop": 1164180,
                                "text": "Our cases make clear that the legislature \u201cmust have discretion to exercise the political judgment necessary to balance competing interest\u201d, and courts must \u201cexercise extraordinary caution in adjudicating claims that a State has drawn district lines on the basis of race.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 267.836,
                                "stop": 275.531,
                                "byte_start": 1164180,
                                "byte_stop": 1194900,
                                "text": "Applying these standards we consider the basic controverted District 12 question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 275.531,
                                "stop": 286.788,
                                "byte_start": 1194900,
                                "byte_stop": 1239935,
                                "text": "Does race rather than politics predominantly explain that District\u2019s 1997 boundaries?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 286.788,
                                "stop": 291.886,
                                "byte_start": 1239935,
                                "byte_stop": 1260311,
                                "text": "The District Court thought that the answer to this question was \u2018yes\u2019."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 291.886,
                                "stop": 297.567,
                                "byte_start": 1260311,
                                "byte_stop": 1283090,
                                "text": "In large part because it found what it believed was not it normally."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 297.567,
                                "stop": 315.749,
                                "byte_start": 1283090,
                                "byte_stop": 1355815,
                                "text": "It believed that the legislature had left some more heavily Democratic nearby precincts outside the district while at the same time it had included other less heavily Democratic precincts inside the district."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 315.749,
                                "stop": 318.067,
                                "byte_start": 1355815,
                                "byte_stop": 1365114,
                                "text": "Why, the court asked."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 318.067,
                                "stop": 332.756,
                                "byte_start": 1365114,
                                "byte_stop": 1423838,
                                "text": "If the legislature was simply trying to create a safe seat for Democrats, would they have included less safe Democratic precincts, while excluding more safe Democratic precincts?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 332.756,
                                "stop": 350.653,
                                "byte_start": 1423838,
                                "byte_stop": 1495413,
                                "text": "The answer must be that it was doing more than simply try to include Democrats and that more sought the District Court involved a predominant motive to include African-Americans, however they might tend to vote."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 350.653,
                                "stop": 372.617,
                                "byte_start": 1495413,
                                "byte_stop": 1583289,
                                "text": "The record however shows that if one measures the Democratic or Republican nature of a precinct by actual voting behavior, rather than simply by party registration, then the legislature in fact did just what the District Court thought it did not do."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 372.617,
                                "stop": 383.785,
                                "byte_start": 1583289,
                                "byte_stop": 1627906,
                                "text": "With very few exceptions, it included the more heavily Democratic precincts and it excluded the less heavily Democratic precincts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 383.785,
                                "stop": 388.088,
                                "byte_start": 1627906,
                                "byte_stop": 1645147,
                                "text": "Thus, there is no anomaly to explain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 388.088,
                                "stop": 396.025,
                                "byte_start": 1645147,
                                "byte_stop": 1676912,
                                "text": "In our opinion, we discuss this matter further and we consider the other evidence before the District Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 396.025,
                                "stop": 415.65,
                                "byte_start": 1676912,
                                "byte_stop": 1755384,
                                "text": "As I have said, we conclude that the plaintiffs, who challenged the District\u2019s boundaries, simply did not satisfy their burden of proof, and applying a clearly erroneous standard of review, we reverse the District Court\u2019s conclusion to the contrary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 415.65,
                                "stop": 425.221,
                                "byte_start": 1755384,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion, which is joined by the Chief Justice, Justice Scalia and Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
